text: I honestly love the dark, serious tone. I feel that all MCU movies will eventually head down this road. It all leads up to Thanos, and he's all about death and destruction, more so than Ultron. Ultron wants to wipe out humans. Thanos wants to wipe out anything that can be considered sentient in the UNIVERSE. I just see Marvel gradually lessening the comedy (maybe except for Guardians of the Galaxy, to keep the humor in there somewhere), the closer we get to Thanos' reign of terror. Quite frankly, I'm all for it.¬†  Oh yeah, this trailer looked badass. Both trailers have had incredibly haunting music, which is refreshing. For those who are complaining about the CGI, the film is still in post-production. They are still polishing things up. A movie like this, it will take a lot of time in the editing room.¬†

text: As someone who is studying vfx and motion design in college breechwascurious is correct in noticing some of the issues in the CGI in this trailer but is incorrect in calling it bad CGI. It is unfinished CGI. Anyone involved within the vfx industry will tell you that it is part of their production pipeline to be still working on shading, lighting, texturing, render passes and composition up until the final week of post production, that is the nature of the business. So breechwascurious don't be so quick to judge until you see the finished product.

There's really nothing else relatable in DC. DC just has a bunch of iconic overpowered superheroes that aren't relatable at all which is why they're having so much trouble making a movie. DC heroes are GODS. Superman, Flash, Martian Manhunter & even Batman is shown in the comics & the movies to be too smart & too strong to be a normal human being. Nuff said. Marvel actually has characters that can die, and can be relatable unlike DC. That's all I got to say about that.

text: I grew up on Marvel and DC, and a crap load of independent comics. I am enjoying the big budget cinematic interpretations of my childhood Super-folk. This trailer is interesting but it doesn't take away my hunger to see Infinity Wars. As for DC I think they need a couple of blockbuster films that are not related to Superman or Batman to truly compete with Marvel.  If Green Lantern was on par with even Thor, I think I would buy into this Marvel vs DC debate. As it stands now it is really just Superman and Batman vs Marvel. I have Semi-hope for Suicide Squad and I really think they may pull out the stops for Aquaman. But as of now, movie-wise, DC feels like a one trick pony. Would love to see Shazam, Black Adam, Doom Patrol, Darkseid and even Omac on the big screen.

text: Alright kids, here are my predictions for Age of Ultron based on the trailer. Again, this is all theoretical.  Also Spoiler alert! Don't read if you aren't up to date with Ultron news.  1. Early in the story, Bruce banner is possessed by the Scarlet Witch, which turns the Hulk on the Avengers. This makes Banner feel guilt and gives for the destruction he's caused and makes him realize no one is safe. 2. While the Avengers are in Johannesburg, Black Panther will be introduced. 3. Ultron will be able to lock into any technology on Earth, making him unstoppable. In order to get rid of Ultron, they have to launch him into orbit. 4. Bruce will sacrifice himself to stop Ultron [This is where the redemption from earlier comes in]. 5. Banner going into orbit can either mean Planet Hulk[squeal], or create the bridge that will lead to a Guardians of the Galaxy/Avengers crossover. 6. Stark will feel guilt that his creation sent one of his best friends into space, prompting him to repent. This will lead to the " Superhuman Registration Act", which will lead to Civil War in Captain America 3.  That's it so far... What are your thoughts?Ôªø

text: The more i see this trailer the more hyped i get. This trailer isn't better then the first... But somehow it just got me more exited then the first one. Ultron ain't messing around! Hes gonna pose a real challange to Thor. And i doubt Hulk will have a as easy go on Ultron as he did Loki. Ultron is just freaking scary... Also love the No strings them playing in the trailer. I really do hope they have it in the movie at some point. Would b kind of fun of they used it as the main theme. But i rather they use it as Ultron's theme tough. Cause The Avengers still has one of the most epic themes ever. Only rivaled by any Hans Zimmer theme. HAHA... But i do hope Age of Ultron gets an equaly epic theme. If not more epic! Guessing it'll be more dark. The Avengers i think is a more lighthearted movie. I think The MCU is moving into some dark theretory now. Clearly the Avengers won't end things on a good note. Thor will leave earth, cap and Tony will have a falling out leading to Civil War in wich they'll be fighting each other... No more friendship. And it'll probably lead to the death of Captain America seeing as hes cause is the most just. And shit will go down... Before Thanos steps up hes game i believe the MCU will allready be out of order to begin with. The heroes won't be friends. Tony will have a new team of Avengers wich he probably won't be as good with as he was the original theme. When they joined forces they became a force to fear. A team with Tony Start (least humble person alive) Doctor Strange (A natural leader) Ant Man (Probably a dick much like Tony) and who ever else... + Tony's gonna have some mental scars after this and Civil War. Age of Ultron will move us into the dark days of the MCU. So i do expect some lighthearted humor.... But this movie won't be anywhere near as lighthearted as The Avengers wich for the most case was a pretty cute and fun movie. It was in part a comdy... Doubt that'll be the case this time around.

text: I reckon the credits scene at the end of this will be something to do with the Illuminati. They already have the members they need; Iron Man, doctor strange had been cast, and Black Bolt is most likely on the way(except Reed Richards, but they could replace him for Black Panther seeing as he's already been cast). In the comics, when Cap discovers that Stark has been part of this secret organisation behind the avengers' and everyone else's back he starts to distrust him and the cracks for Civil War begin to show (which is a confirmed for phase 3). Hopefully if this is right, we should be seeing a Planet Hulk movie, or at least a set up for it. Just as Civil war is starting to begin, the Illuminati trick Bruce Banner into boarding a spacecraft thinking he's on a repairment mission, when in fact they've planned the coordinates for a planet inhabited only by unintelligent life-forms. This leads to Planet Hulk and then World War hulk. So this makes sense for a few reasons; the first being that we definitely know Hulk loses it in Age of Ultron and fights Stark himself, meaning he'll probably lose the trust of his team members and bring Stark to make the decision to banish him. Secondly, the Hulk doesn't play a part in Civil war, he's up in space living out the Planet Hulk storyline on Sakaar. So this would be a possible route for hulk while the Civil War goes on; then he would return to Earth when the war ends to crack some Illuminati skulls. Finally, Marvel has announced movies for all of the Illuminati characters involved in the Planet Hulk and World War Hulk storylines (apart from Mr Fantastic who can be replaced by the confirmed Black Panther as I already mentioned). You gotta wonder what the reason is for making movies for these specific characters, and one thing they all have in common is they're members of the Illuminati.  Or I could be completely wrong and have just wasted 5 minutes of my life typing all of that.

text: I case anybody here sees the guy below that's asking for a leaked movie site or the "Free steam wallet codes!!" don't be fooled.  *This is done by a group of people working together!*  The guy asking for leaked movies? He posts that on lost of videos, and another guy has done the same with the exact same wording funnily enough. And the same site came up at the end, but it's nothing but a hoax. *These people reply to each other and like their comments so that more people see the comment and more people fall into the Hack-Trap.*  Same with the "Money Generators" that you've been seeing alot recently. Funny that they want you to download something to give you free money at no benefit to them from sites that have no ads and little revenue. Why would they spread this without fear of being found by the proper authorities? Why wouldn't amazon track them down and stop them? *Because these don't work and Amazon/Steam/PSN/ etc aren't threatened.*  All those thumbs up and replies saying "This worked great!" they're done by people who go from video to video *just to comment the exact same thing.* It's just an elaborate hoax built on the "trust-by-numbers" system we've grown accustomed to on the internet. I encourage you not to give in.  Please thumb this up so we can stop this.

text: Meh, I've totally lost all of my enthusiasm for The Avengers and the MCU. They've just deviated way too far from the source material and upended the entire¬†Avengers mythology for no good reason other than to shoehorn the square peg that was Edgar Wright's incompatible 2004 Ant Man script into the round hole that is the Marvel Universe. No Hank Pym as Ant Man/Giant¬†Man/Yellowjacket¬†or Janet Van Dyne as The Wasp¬†in the Avengers; no Hank Pym creating Ultron, which is his central storyline; Tony Stark having everything revolve around him, as usual,¬†including creating Ultron and The Vision, neither of which were his creations at all. This might as well not even be The Avengers anymore, this is just Kevin Feige's sloppy¬†cut-and-paste job. And don't give me that "movies can't be like the comics" crap, because that's just making excuses for lazy, sloppy,¬†unimaginative¬†filmmaking. The Lord of the Rings, The Hunger Games, and the Harry Potter films were all much more faithful to the source material, and they still managed to be great, successful films.

text: First off this trailer looks amazing I'm so hyped for this movie I know it's gonna blow are minds!!! I am both a Marvel and DC fan so now that being said I'm really tired of this constant fight between Marvel and DC fans going back in forth like it's unnecessary I don't know why people would want to start shit on why this movie sucks or why Marvel is better then DC vice/versa like come on people were at an age where we are finally getting good comic book movies that we never thought we would see on the big screen. Back in the early 2000s we had some good and some bad comic book movies and it started to get really good when Nolan came to work on Batman Begins and The Dark Knight and then Marvel came out with Iron Man and planned out their slate of movies in their Cinematic Universe. Yea they may had miss steps with Iron Man 2 and and the Incredible Hulk but they learned from their mistakes and listen to fans so that they can do the best they can to make more better films. Yes Everybody knows Marvel Studios started their slate first and have had 10 movies come out and have proven to us that they can be a well trusted brand with their movies but that doesn't give us the right to say they suck or that DC is the better brand or that Marvel movies are overrated. I understand that everybody has their own opinion but it shouldn't give you the right to talk shit and talk about how the Marvel Cinematic Universe sucks ass and all just be proud that they made it this far and and at least have respect for them for working their ass off to create this wonderful universe. As for The DC Cinematic Universe they are just starting to build their universe up by starting with Superman. I understand that people are mixed on that movie and I respect y'all's opinions but at least they are trying. And you have to remember it was coming off of Superman Returns which at the time people didn't really think it was that good but now their opinions may have changed but for the most part Man of Steel was successful and they are now trying to really kick it off with Batman V. Superman and Suicide Squad. We may have not liked what Warner Bros./DC in the past but at least they are trying to give you the character that you want to see on the big screen cause they could have given up after 2011 Green Lantern but they didn't so let's just stop saying DC is rushing cause they are clearly not rushing. The studio obviously wants to take their time to make the best films that they can possibly make. Just be happy for DC and respect them to keep trying and working hard so that we can get the films that we fans deserve. We may not always agree with each studios decisions on what they do or plan but we should respect them and be happy that we can get the movies of are favorite characters. I don't kno what they are gonna do with Spiderman but I just hope Marvel and Sony can come to an agreement that will let us see the we slinger again on the big screen.

text: Watching this makes me want to say one thing to Marvel: Please don't decrease the quality of your movies. I'm not at all saying this movie looks bad to me, I mean the opposite! I just don't want future movies to start doing bad because I love these movies and can't wait for Phase 3 and the characters in it, such as Doctor Strange, Black Panther, Captain Marvel, and Inhumans. But when a company gets so successful, they can lose sight of what got them there. And I really don't want any of these movies to fall in the: "We're so successful so we'll make bad movies and make money anyway" category. Besides, that hasn't worked out for certain other movies.¬†  All I'm saying is, Marvel is awesome and I want them to make movies with the same intent as Iron Man 1 from 2008: To simply make a good movie, no matter what it takes. Never try to add more than what you guys feel makes the story work JUST to please the fans. Because sometimes, trying to please the fans in certain ways can fail (Spider-Man 3 and The Amazing Spider-Man 2). The good part about Avengers: Age of Ultron is that I feel this is very much Joss Whedon (and Kevin Feige/Marvel) expressing himself creatively to make a good movie, with compelling characters and an engaging plot.

text: I find it funny that all the DC fans are saying, "You didn't like Man of Steel's over the top destruction but you are ok with this?"  Put it into perspective. Man of Steel ended with about half of Metropolis in RUINS. The fight between the Hulkbuster and the Hulk (as shown in this trailer at least) shows a street being wrecked with some cars being blown up and thrown around, with civilians in the midst of the fight (like Man of Steel by the way). In terms of Destruction, Man of Steel surpassed even the first Avengers film.¬†  Also to those who will say I'm a Marvel fanboy, here are my favorite comic books from my own collection. I'll even make a video on my channel for those who doubt the validity.  Batman: Court of Owls Storyline (best of the New 52 IMO and he's batman. My fave DC hero) Flash Volume 1 (New 52. Mainly cause I like Captain Cold) Flashpoint (Great comic and Great animated movie) Justice League Volume 1 (Didn't care for Hal Jordan. He was more of a dick than pre 52.) Age of Ultron (The time travel aspect is confusing, but it's a good read) Avengers: Children's Crusade (Young Avengers FTW) Fear Itself: The Invincible Iron Man (Favorite Marvel Hero) Armor Wars (Iron Man....nuff said)  So yeah, I'm not a butthurt DC fanboy, nor am I just a Marvel fan. I love BOTH.

text: I'm sick and tired of people saying they're sick and tired of comic book/superhero films. When are these people going to realize that it's a genre in the exact same way as science fiction, fantasy, or horror? Have you ever heard someone say "there's too many science fiction films coming out nowadays, the market is going to be so over-saturated"? Never! The good films will rise to the top and the bad films will fall to obscurity the same as any other genre. The best part: If you don't enjoy the genre, you don't have to watch the films.

text: Predictions for Avengers 2 just based on the trailers and a life time of reading comics:  #1 Hulk is not being mind controlled because that's nearly impossible seeing how it's one of his natural abilities as a raging monster. He is simply under an Illusion Spell by the mysterious Asgardian woman in Thor's scene. It is hard to mind control Hulk, but he's easy to trick/confuse.  #2 The Asgargian woman is Karnilla (Queen of Nornhiem). She specializes in illusion casting and has enchantments to help improve her illusion powers. I believe she traps Thor somehow to take him out of the equation and then goes and casts an Illusion spell on Banner/Hulk to see his teammates and people in the city as a threat to him. Karnilla believe no one can stop Hulk seeing how Thor is trapped/incapacitated. So Tony has to call in his secret weapon the Hulk Buster armor.¬†  #3 If an Avenger dies I think it will be Black Widow. Reason I say this is because she has been seen in enough movies to where the audience would feel the impact of the characters death. Plus this would free up a slot for Black Panther to take her place on the team. It might be Hawkeye who dies, but he really hasn't had enough screen time that the audience would feel this loss. If one of them doesn't die then I just don't see Marvel killing anyone on the team seeing how most of the super powered heroes have more movies coming out.  #4 The woman on the surgery table is Scarlet Witch. She and Quicksilver I believe will be experimented on to see how there powers work. This makes them hate humanity and decide to join Ultron to whip out the humans. Later on of course they will see the error of there ways and join the Avengers as reserve members.

text: After seeing this trailer and the one before it, I have to say that I'm starting to get worried ¬†about the fight between "The Hulkbuster Suit" and "The Hulk."  When I think of a fight between these two icons I think of some seriously raw, balls-to-the-wall brawling with a multitude of destructible objects getting obliterated every second. ¬†What I'm seeing from the first trailer and this one is the notion that the fight will be rather epic, but in a neutered/tame way, as if those in charge operating behind the scenes were afraid of offending the audience if they had a fight sequence that had the hulk and hulk buster crashing straight through buildings and potentially killing innocents. ¬†All we've seen from the trailers show us that the entire fight is taking place (conveniently/lazily) on the streets were the carnage (conveniently/lazily) can't get too out of hand. ¬† *I get that Tony Stark would try and keep casualties low but that's a massive stretch when you add the Hulk into the fray.*  I honestly want and hope that both the movie and this signature fight will surpass expectations but I can't help but feel reserved.

text: Hello fans. Im just here to speculate and find out your opinions on what is going on regarding the avengers. Example at 1:03 thor looks to be channelling some lightning and shooting it at someone to me, because ive always known he can use his powers without his hammer. Remember this is part 2 so they have to always one up their powers from previous movies. But some say he looks like hes being electrocuted(<<lol) or hes having his powers taken away. What are your thoughts on this?¬†  Electrocuting the god of thunders seems highly unlikely, but we see him in what appears to be asgard, and we know that loki is impersonating odin at the moment, could he be using the all fathers powers to¬†weaken him or strip him of his powers like in thor 1? He seems to have odins staff which can do all sorts. I still think hes just shooting someone though, because the energy originated from his body and he shoots it out of the right arm towards something judging by its trajectory. Again could just be clever editing to TRICK US. Some say thor might die in this movie, maybe just temporarily, any thoughts on this?  Regarding the hulk what do you think is going on with him, hulk has never truly been evil, usually kills when attacked and his eyes looked red. Im guessing it has something to do with mind control, maybe scarlet witch? I know its not really her powers but its not the first time MCU has changed a characters powers/origin.¬†  Would like to know what others think

text: So let's sum up what the avengers trailer tells us: Tony had been experimenting with newer technologies prior to the 3rd movie and when his home was attacked they were mostly ruined. However, not all of it was, one suit had an advanced AI which incorporated parts of Jarvis, then using an arc reactor he had built into one of the suits, was able to begin bettering itself.¬† It manages to escape and begin causing trouble in the surrounding area. Tony reveals this is kinda sorta his fault which pisses everyone off, however, they set aside their differences and try to do the crime fighting thing. The machine perfects itself though and includes a viral imprinting system of some kind that causes the hulk to go on a rampage. Since the Hulk is pretty much unbeatable, thor gets owned, the cap gets owned and tony switches out suits and uses the hulk beater armor to fight him. Black widow manages to stop him somehow (likely cause the big guy trusts widow) and...what? they fight ultron and his new robot army and win?  Did I miss any other obvious plot points?

text: This sucks. Hank Pym as Yellowjacket¬†was the one who took Ultron down in the comics, yet Hank¬†has no part of the Ultron storyline, a saga¬†in which he and Janet Van Dyne/The Wasp¬†were central figures in the comics?¬†Instead, Tony Stark will be responsible for Ultron's creation; D-list character Scott Lang will be the face of Ant Man, and Hank Pym's Giant Man persona will not exist;¬†Hank's Yellowjacket persona will instead be adopted by a villain; Janet Van Dyne will be dead and a non-existent daughter named Hope will replace her; and Hank will be made into a 70 year old man in the movies, even though he's supposed to be the same age as Tony Stark or younger? That's a lot of Marvel and Avengers mythology upended just to shoehorn the square peg that was Edgar Wright's old and Avengers-incompatible Ant Man script into the round hole that is the Marvel universe. It wasn't worth throwing Hank and Janet under the bus just for some British filmmaker who hasn't done anything anyone's cared about since Shaun of the Dead in 2004, and who only ended up leaving the project anyway. Hank and Janet deserved better.

text: Its interesting how many negative comments there are about this unreleased movie. Funny thing is, that 99% of all the people posting them will still end up paying to go see Avengers when it comes out; even after stating how much they hated the previous films, or how garbage they think the new ones look. You have to admit how impressive it is that Marvel makes films so high quality and wildly popular that even the haters go to see them. At the end of the day, these people still end up handing over their money....Marvel wins. So if you're going to see the film no matter how much you belittle it, why not try to have a more open-minded expectation?

text: This trailer reminds me of the sequel to Michael Bay's Transformers (the first one). A bunch of cyborgs battling it out and cinematic cgi crap everywhere you look. As a Marvel fan, I must say I am heavily disappointed at where they've taken these fellow superheroes.¬† When I was in elementary school, it was cool to be into Spiderman, the Hulk, Wolverine, Thor, and Captain America.¬† It seems though in the past five years they've really toned it down with everything. Kind of like the WWE (World Wrestling Entertainment). It used to be cool to watch, back in the 80s and 90s during the attitude era. Once the ratings began to go up, the executives decided--- for the sake of money and apparently their survival in the industry, they had to tone it down so that children could watch it with their families.¬† That is exactly what's happened to Marvel in the last few years.  Does anyone agree with me?

text: Instead of viewing this as a movie trailer of a film which you may or may not go and see (or download), see it for what it is: a symbolic expression of our time constituting a kind of apocalyptic vision. To recognize this all you need to do is to see it alongside so many other similiar visions which share as their core elements the themes of the superhero, the nemesis, hubris calling forth its nemesis, interdimensional invasion (aliens, a kind of alien-intelligence, an organic-machine, or an abstract evil which somehow steals into the world), the man-machine.

text: The Marvel Studios Secret looks to be in full effect in this movie. ¬†This is very exciting! ¬†I wonder if the tension can be maintained and built over a year or more of high-priced promotion (of course, it will, you guys are pros). ¬†All these promos are most assuredly building to a big pay-off, and, like most people, I can hardly wait. ¬†One point for future promos, though: there has to be another part of the GD soundtrack that can achieve the same effect. ¬†In the first trailer, that was awesome; in the second trailer, it began to grow an association, but by now, it's tiresome and distracting, and I'm sure you don't want to build an association with a melody whose arrangement gets downright hokey at the end and will more than likely not even feature in the film. ¬†Otherwise, my calendar is marked for this one. ¬†I would thank you, but you'll more than likely get my box office admission money for this one, and that's thanks enough.

text: I'm pumped as hell for this movie, but it worries me how many side plots they are trying to squeeze into only 2-3 hours. The change of Ultron to his final form, the introduction of Quicksilver and Scarlet Witch, the introduction of things related to Black Panther (and even himself), the introduction of the Vision, the introduction of Andy Serkis as a possible future villain, the start of the falling out between Tony Stark and Steve Rodgers for Civil War, the backstory for Black Widow, possibly the set up for the third Thor movie, a possible future link between Antman and the Avengers, and so much more! All these things are so vital to the MCU, and it seems like a lot for one movie. I just hope they pull it off.

text: Okay, the Marvel Cinematic Universe under Kevin Feige has become a total god-awful mess. I totally understand having to work around Sony and¬†Fox owning the film rights to Spider-Man, X-Men, and Fantastic Four, but Marvel could've certainly done a better job than this! Making Hank Pym a 70 year-old man and having Scott Lang be the main character of Ant-Man? Eliminating Hank Pym and Janet Van Dyne from both the Avengers and the Ultron storylines, of which they are central characters in the comics? No Hank Pym as Ant-Man/Giant-Man when he's vastly more powerful and cinematically appealing at both microscopic size and 100 feet in height than goofy-ass Paul Rudd as Scott Lang? No Janet Van Dyne as The Wasp, who is not only one of the most popular female characters in Marvel comics, but is a co-founding member of the Avengers along with Hank, and would bring a much-needed female presence to the mostly male-dominated MCU?  And they're¬†making Quicksilver and Scarlet Witch Inhumans instead of mutants, which is one of the laziest, most unimaginative decisions I've yet seen? The simpler solution that fits in with Wanda and Pietro's origin story is to have them be the genetically-engineered offspring of the High Evolutionary, as they were both born at his complex at Wundagore Mountain. If they can have Thanos in the MCU, why not the Evolutionary? And having The Vision¬†and Ultron created by Tony Stark is¬†yet again more laziness on the part of Kevin Feige. Let's just give all the storylines to Robert¬†Downey Jr., huh? ¬†

text: Seeing Hulk's (quite interesting) expression in this, I had a feeling, which led to a theory.¬†  He could very well have just saved Natasha's life at that moment.  And I mean, I'm really just speculating here, but his gaze really fascinates me. He looks as though he just had a workout (be it with the HulkBuster or an actual enemy, that is unknown) and is exhausted, and yet, he takes the time to really just stop and focus his energy on her, all the while looking strangely transfixed, but surprisingly calm at the same time. Could that be residual worry, or even relief?¬† She too seems to be considering him, although with an entirely different and very intense expression, and I may be wrong on this but she really has the face of someone who just had a brush with death... and is perfectly aware of it. Or at the very least, who is in serious shock, most likely of something that previously happened (whatever that may be). Now, there would be NO logical reason whatsoever for her to be standing that close to him. We all know there is no way, in hell, she would ever dare willingly approach him, so to see them actually facing each other is indeed peculiar. But what makes this part so intriguing to me is that she isn't running away either. Instead of just plain afraid, she rather appears troubled and deep in thought. And emotionally shaken, that's for sure. Something tells me that she may, at some point, be forced to reconsider everything she had thought she knew about the Hulk in this movie, and the perspective of seeing her finally overcome her fear of him, as well as the two getting to understand and respect each other makes me REALLY excited for this movie. :D Now I can tell there will be some awesome developpement in this, no matter what direction it takes!

text: Who isn't hype for this movie? In guessing it'll be the most popular movie this year. Here are some of my theories on who'll die, now I'm pretty sure they'll make it a very surprising death, meaning one of the more important characters. Hulk- Why he may die? He and Black widow will have a thing going on, and if he dies, it'll be a tragic love story.  Why may he not die? He's practically impossible to kill when he's in hulk mode. Black Widow- Same like Hulk, tragic love story.  Why may she not die? She is confirmed to be in Captain America-Civil War, and she's pretty swift. That's all my reasoning for her. Captain America- He is confirmed for another movie, but what if the movie( Civil War ) takes place in the past? He may die but thats higly unlikely to me, but honestly, he has no actual super power so he has a higher chance of dying, plus he is the most willing avenger to give up his life. Thor- In one scene, he's in a "pool" probably in another realm, but he is practically a "God" but what if the "pool" isn't water but something that can kill him, it's highly unlikely but it's a theory. Iron man- He's confirmed for another movie, true that he has no power, he can fight hulk, hulk is hard to kill... and has upgraded his suit, adding on to that, he is practically a "main" character in the movie. Hawkeye- Likely to die midway during the movie, but like i said at the beginning, Marvel probably wants a shocking death, he could die but another avenger might die too. Quicksilver and Scarlet witch-Scarlet witch, can be seen in a scene crying in the trailer, both of them were fighting with Ultron at first but in the end, you see Scarlet fighting with the avengers, maybe Ultorn has killed Quicksilver and made her switch sides. Who do you think will die?  Personally I think, Hulk or Thor...

text: The Soul Gem (1/5 of the Infinity Stones) Is in the Visions Forehead. the Vision was created by Ultron, Ultron Created by Stark(In the movie) Stark¬† was in possession of Loki's Scepter, but Loki's scepter contained the Mind Gem, which had to mean Stark was in possession of both at one point until after Ultron was created and he stole/took the Mind Gem which he used to create Vision with...  assuming I am correct..¬†  In the final act of the movie we will have the original Avengers, Vision, Scarlet and Quicksilver, pitted against one of the final upgrade of Ultron (Adimantium/Vibranium version) and Ullyses Claw if he hasnt been defeated or killed.  Ultron will eventually be defeated, not killed off for good, but defeated for now.  Thor will die (along with someone less powerful maybe one of the twins).. Setting the story for Thor: Ragnorak  a problem will arise between Cap & Stark setting the story for Captain America: Civil War and a HUGE twist, surprise or cameo for the fate of every ones world, humans, asgardians, mutants, aliens, will be announced or fore-seen.¬†  Maybe made by the presence of a bigger villain(Thanos) or someone in connection with him.  Aside from these characters, we have stories for AntMan, Doctor Strange and Guardians Coming out in between Avengers 2 & Avengers 3(Infinity Gauntlet)  My guess is(assuming im still correct) These are introductions, additions and adaptations that will play a part in the story for Infinity gauntlet where all these characters or their actions in the films, will contribute to the battle the future group of Avengers & Guardians will have against Thanos & his group of Villains  We know Doctor Strange brings a dead hero back to life and the villains he fights in the movie will also be pitted against the then Avengers as well.  AntMan or his technology/story will help the Avengers sometime in the future or just further explains the origin of the programming Stark jump started to become Ultron.  In the upcoming Gaurdians 2, one possible villian along with the Collector and Nebula is Warlock, but it can as well be any one of the evil characters Collector has strung up in his lab, which we all know was almost completely destroyed or made a mess of in Guardians, allowing for the release or awakening of those villains along with any powerful weapons or items he had.  Thus, allowing Thanos to recruit and assemble a group to take on the heroes of the universe and kill off anyone who opposes his will. Meanwhile back on Earth, Avengers team will be introducing Black Panther officially to the roster with him fighting his own battles or whatever with maybe even Ullyses Claw making a comeback from being defeated in Age of Ultron (assuming he wasn't killed or even assuming if my theory of that movie is correct smh) There will need to be a huge surprise or event in the ending of Black Panthers battles that either will leave him as a official member of Avengers to await or join the battle against Thanos or will have a connection/lead to Captain Marvel.  Captain Marvel has always butt heads with Thanos very often, so it wouldn't be a surprise if Captain takes a lead in the battle against him, letting the rest of the Avengers to handle other villains less powerful or for them to gather the necessary means to defeat Thanos.  In which that will lead up to Avengers 4(Infinity Gauntlet 2) Where its every hero vs a villain or a couple of the universes most powerful heroes to go against Thanos as a full fledged god with a very complete Infinity Gauntlet.  NOW assuming I am correct or very close to getting the story and events right, Thanos will be defeated but not killed( maybe he will be killed idk thats up to how they change his fate in the movie version of the comics) Most of the heroes will have perished in the fight and like fallout from a nuclear war, the use the Infinity Stones or contact with, will have an affect on a group of experimented humans which will then be the rise of the Inhumans and the start of a new Marvel Phase.  Before I get any backlash I am completely aware that my theory can turn out to be completely and utterly wrong but its fun trying to piece together and figure out how these events and movies will play out :) It gives you something to think about until we actually see what happens !

text: Thor challenges others to lift the hammer, none can do it apart from Cap managed to shift it very slightly which he doesn't notice and Black Widow declines to try. Vision lifts the hammer later on. We see Black Widow's back-story more, she was from some assassin school or something and apparently she was sterilized. There was a lot of Black Widow/Hulk romance stuff which came out of nowhere a little but it worked pretty well. Hawkeye has a wife and kids which he was keeping secret. Ultron is an alright villain but was lacking in character beyond generic Whedon quipping. At the end Cap assembles a bunch of new members for the Avengers including Scarlet Witch, Falcon, War Machine and one more if I'm remembering correctly. Quicksilver dies saving Hawkeye. It ends setting up Thor seeking Ragnorok and Cap doubting Stark's ability to resist tampering futher with the world, and Hulk goes AWOL on his own. Post-credits scene shows Thanos putting on the gauntlet and saying 'I'll have to do it myself' or something. No second post-credits scene. It was shit lol.

text: Warning: Spoilers!      The movie begins with the Avengers retrieving Loki's staff from a still existing Hydra base. Tony uses iron man robots (like in Ironman 3) to evacuate a nearby city. People reject the robots. The Avengers get the staff and return to the Avengers Tower. Tony and Bruise discover a way to create artificial intelligence, and Tony and Bruce create a new intelligence to implement into Ultron, who would work along side the Avengers. Later that night a party would be hosted in celebration of retrieving the staff.      Ultron awakes without a body, Jarvis notices he is malfunctioning and acts him to reboot, but Ultron rejects Jarvis's request and kills him. Ultron implants himself in one of the iron man robots.      After the party is over, you see the Avengers sitting down talking and telling stories. They all attempt to lift Thor's hammer. After each one of them tried, Thor tells them they're simply not worthy to wield the hammer. Then Ultron walks into the room, limping. Ultron explains his purpose and the only way to peace is the Avenger's extinction. Several Ultron Bots fly the the walls and attack the avengers. Thor throws his hammer at Ultron, destroying him. Ultron escapes into the Internet. The Avengers discover that Jarvis is dead, they blame Tony.     We see Quick Silver and Scarlet Witch walk into a chapel, in the center Ultron sits on a throne with his new armor. He explains his purpose once again and asks them why they let the Avengers take the staff.     The Avengers track them down to a pear. Ultron, Quick Silver, and Scarlet Witch take Vibranium to make Vision, but are caught by  the Avengers. The Avengers attack Ultron, QS and SW. During the fight, SW puts several of the Avengers under a trance. When she does it to Hulk, he rampages to a nearby city. Because all of the Avengers are either wounded are under a trance, Tony uses the Hulk Buster to stop hulk. Tony stops Hulk but destroys nearly half the city (possibly leaving a reason for a civil war) News spreads, and Bruce is endangered of getting arrested. They fly to a safe house and stay there for a few weeks     Ultron brakes into the Avengers tower and uses a regeneration machine and uses the Vibranium to create Vision. SW scans the Vision body and discovers Ultron's true plans. Instead of getting rid of just the Avengers, he planned to get rid of all of humanity. SW and QS betray Ultron. The Avengers show up at the tower to stop Ultron. Ultron flees but with Black Widow. Tony and Bruce discovers Jarvis was still alive and fled into the Internet as well. Tony decides to put the conscious of Jarvis in the lifeless Vision body, but Captain America walks in to tell them not to do that because what happened to Ultron might happen to Vision. They argue until Thor appears from the sky and brings Vision to life with an mind infinity stone. Vision reveals to the Avengers he is on their side and wishes to stop Ultron because he is the real threat, not the Avengers.     Ultron his bots invade Nova Scotia, Ultron raises a piece of the city into the sky, he plans to use it as a metaphor for a meteor and plans to drop it to the Earth wiping out humanity. Ultron does just that, taking the city into the sky, but the Avngers are there to stop him. After fighting off the bots, ten helicarrier shows up and takes the people of the city, the Avengers take advantage of the fact that the people have been taken out of the city and destroy it, but before that, Ultron steals jet begins firing at the Avengers, Hawkeye  was going to risk his life to save a little boy, but before Uktron shot him, quick silver used himself as a shield for Hawkeye and dies, Scarlet kills Ultron by removing his "heart." Thor destroys the city as if fell to the Earth.     You see vision and the last Ultron bot standing on a hill. Vision questions the bot and then kills the bot, destroying Ultron once and for all.   The after credit scene is Thanos picking up the goblet which is missing all the Infinity Stones, as he smirks at the camera. (This is literally 5 seconds)   If some of this didn't make sense, it's either I forgot or I just have poor writing skills. Also, some information was excluded from this, so.

text: With the football season over , the next best thing to do on Saturday afternoon is take in a film so the kids dragged me along to see Avengers: Age of Ultron. While i found it entertaining and the special affects were great as usual , this is pretty much just more of the same as the last film. It's funny in parts but nowhere near as much as Guardians of the Galaxy but the thing that really struck me was the product placement. It's staggeringly blatant. My 12 year old son asked me afterwords , "if they are all superheroes and they have all the mind blowing gadgets , why are they driving Audi's and using Samsung tablets?" . He has a point because It did look like one big entertaining commercial.¬† This killed a few hours on a football-less afternoon but it won't stay long in the memory.  6 out of 10

text: My quick review:   Visuals and CGI was excellent. Acting was average or below average. Natasha whats her name was good, and the voice of the robot was good. That robot looked lifted right from Terminator Salvation. Captain America that actor did not play this role well. Samuel Jackson again plays the all-knowing omnipotent wise man who talks down to everyone.   The worst part of this movie was that it didn't take itself NEARLY seriously enough. Tons of cheesy and goofy punch-lines¬†all during¬†dramatic moments, which took so much away from it. Never seen so much corny humor in a comic-book movie like EVER.   I would give the action a 10/10. As far as acting, no one really was that good except the Natasha woman. Wayyy too much corny dialogue. I mean I realize it is supposed to be a fun movie... The Hulk, most Iron Man movies, the first Avengers and Captain America all felt way more like true full-fledged comic book movies. I felt nothing for the actors and with the cheap one-liners, seems like they wanted to appeal to everyone. Wouldn't have been surprised if it would have been rated PG.

text: *We all have deep questions.*  _What is the meaning of life? Why are we here? What happens after death? Is there anything we can do to go to a better place? What is my calling in life? text: For those wondering who "kitty" is, I'll explain:  kitty0706 was a YouTuber from long ago, famous for creating GMod videos. His most popular work was a GMod video called "Team Fabulous 2", which to this day has garnered over 19 million views.  I've no clue when he was first diagnosed with cancer, I think it was 2012, but his leukemia grew serious and he was forced to spend more time away from YouTube. He died on January 25, 2015, and boy, I remember that day fairly well. I was sitting in my high school science classroom (that's where I ate at lunch with my friends) and was scrolling through some stuff, and decided to watch a kitty0706 video. So I type his name into the internet browser, and it comes up with a reddit post about his death. I screamed "WHAT THE F---" and everybody in the room turned and stared at me. I had only been a fan of kitty for about a year, maybe even less, but I couldn't believe it. I thought (and I think everyone else did) that he was pretty much done with leukemia and he was doing okay, but it all kind of sprung on us...  Looking back, I actually think kitty0706 was one of the most sane and kindhearted people on YouTube (especially with the drama going on right now), and many memorial videos that came out afterwards from friends and acquaintances seemed to portray that too. Regardless, this felt like a huge loss for a lot of TF2 and GMod video fans.  Apparently, this was the last video kitty0706 liked on his account, so that's why so many confused people (myself included) wound up from his channel. If you want to see if you'd like any of his stuff, it's kind of an acquired taste, but try Team Fabulous 2 and the Moments with Heavy series.  RIP kitty0706
